Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: CITY HALL at Broadway,  Park Row and Chambers Street. It is the seat of government of the great metropolis and can be visited by the public from 10 o'clock A. M. to 4 P. M. daily.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: CENTRAL PARK,  which is the largest park in the city is located at 5th Avenue and Central Park West, 59th to 110th Streets. It contains 862 acres of which is water. It is 2 1/2 miles long and half a mile wide. It contains a Zoological Park and many play grounds.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE AQUARIUM, located at the Battery, can be reached by all subway and elevated lines. The exhibit includes all kinds of fish, both salt and fresh water also invertebrates. Open daily: hours 9 to 5 P. M. April to September, and 9 A. M. to 4 P. M. October to March. The admission is free. The New York Aquarium is probably the largest in the world and has the largest collection of fish. It contains 7 large pools and 144 glass fronted aquarias.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: COOPER UNION-MUSEUM FOR THE ARTS OF DECORATION,  Cooper Square at 7th St., Open daily except Sundays, 10 - 5., evenings, Oct. 1 - 6:30 - 9:30 Except Saturdays and Sundays. Free.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: CLOISTERS,  The Branch of Metropolitan Museum of Art, Fort Tyron Park. Hrs: 10 - 5., Sundays 1 - 6., Closed Christmas Morning. Free except Mon. and Fri. 25c. Hrs. 8 to dusk; Sundays and Holidays 10 to dusk; Library closed on Sat., July

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: NEW YORK ZOOLOGICAL PARK,  Bronx Park - Hrs. 10 to dusk every day. Free except Mondays and Thursday Adults 25c, Children 15c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: NEW YORK BOTANICAL GARDEN,  East of 200th St., and Webster Avenue. Hrs. March 1 to November 1, 10 to 5; November to March 1, 10 to 4:30.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: NEW YORK MUSEUM OF SCIENCE AND INDUSTRY,  R. C. A. Bldg., Rockefeller Center. Hrs: 10 to 10 every day. Adults 25c., Children 10c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: AMERICAN MUSEUM OF NATURAL HISTORY,  Central Park West at 79th St. Hrs: 9 to 5; Sunday 1 to 5. Free

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: AMERICAN GEOGRAPHICAL SOCIETY,  Broadway at 156th St. Hrs: 9 to 4:45 Closed Sundays and Holidays: and on Saturdays during the summer.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: MUSEUM OF THE CITY OF NEW YORK,  Fifth Avenue at 104th St. Hrs:    10 - 5, Sundays 1 - 5. Closed Tuesdays. Free except Mondays 25c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: MUSEUM OF THE NUMISMATIC SOCIETY, Broadway between 155th - 156th Sts. Hrs: 2 - 5 Daily and Sundays. Closed July 16 to Sept., 1, Free.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: MUSEUM OF THE AMERICAN INDIAN,  Heye Foundation, Broadway at 155th St. Hrs. 2 - 5. Closed Sundays, Holidays and through July and August.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: HAMILTON GRANGE,  287 Convent Avenue. Hrs: 10 - 5; Saturdays 10 - 1. Closed Sundays and Holidays. Free

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: WHITNEY MUSEUM OF AMERICAN ART,  10 West 8th St. Hrs. Tuesday to Friday, 1 - 5; Saturday and Sunday 2 - 6. Closed Mondays and Midsummer Months. Reopens about September 15. Free

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: PIERPONT MORGAN LIBRARY, 33   East 36th St. Hrs: Main Bldg., Tues. and Thusdays, 11 - 4; Exhibition Room, Daily 10 - 5. Closed Sundays, Holidays and July 1 to Sept. 7. Free.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: MUSEUM OF LIVING ART,  Fifth Avenue at 82nd St. Hrs. - 10 - 5, Sundays 1 - 6., Closed Christmas Morning. Free except Mondays and Fridays. 25c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: FRICK COLLECTION, 1 East 70th St. Hrs., Sundays and Holidays 1 - 5. Closed Mondays, Decoration Day, July 4th, Month of August and Christmas. Free.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: CONEY ISLAND,  New York's own seaside recreation resort is ten miles from New York City. Here one will find bathing and all sorts of open air amusements

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: BROOKLYN MUSEUM  Eastern Parkway and Washington Avenue, Brooklyn. Hrs: 10 - 5., Sundays 2 - 6., Free except Mon. and Fri. Adults 25c Children 10c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: BROOKLYN BOTANIC GARDEN,  1000 Washington Ave., Brooklyn; Garden Hrs. 8 to dusk; Sundays and Holidays 10 to dusk; Library closed on Sat., July 15 - Sept. 15. Hrs; Mon. to Fri 9 - 5., Saturdays 9 - 12. Free.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING is the tallest office building in the world and is situated at 5th Avenue between 33rd and 34th Streets. The site is nearly 2 acres and rises 102 stories above the ground and is 2 stories under the ground. It houses more than 25.000 tenants. Its elevators rise at the tremendous speed of 200 feet per second. While its express cars carry one to the 80th floor in one minute.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: ELLIS ISLAND is the first landing place of the immigrant and is located in the upper bay of New York harbor. This island may be visited by securing a pass from the Commissioner of Immigration.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: CATHEDRAL OF ST. JOHN THE DIVINE, located at Amsterdam Avenue 110th to 113th Streets, is America's greatest church edifice. When completed it will be the largest Gothic Cathedral in the world. The seating capacity is 15,000 and room for 40,000 standing. It has been in the building for the last 61 years the corner stone being laid in 1892. Visitors are always welcome and services are held practically all day.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE GEORGE WASHINGTON BRIDGE, over the Hudson River, is the longest suspension bridge in the East, connecting New York City at 179th Street and Fort Lee, N. J. It is used by millions of people annualy, and is the Northern route to motorists going South from the North. Its towers, which stand 80 feet higher than the Washington Monument can be seen for miles around. The New York Tower has the "Will Rogers Mem-orial Beacon," which serves as a guide to aviators.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE THEATRICAL DISTRICT OF NEW YORK, where all of the largest and best plays are staged and produced, is located in the heart of the city. Here you will find the largest and best showhouses in the world from 39th to 52nd Streets and 8th to 6th Ave.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE GENERAL POST OFFICE is the largest post office in the world. It covers 2 city blocks from 31st Street to 33rd and from 8th to 9th Avenue. It houses 18,000 employees, makes 26 collections and 3 to 4 deliveries a day.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE HOLLAND TUNNEL is the busiest vehicular tunnel in the world. Starts at Canal Street in New York and ends at 12th Street, Jersey City; N. J. This tunnel contains 2 tubes; one for West bound and the other for East bound traffic; each 2 tubes wide. The toll is 50c per car.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE TRI-BOROUGH BRIDGE, which connects three of the boroughs of Greater New York (Manhattan, Bronx, Queens). This bridge is 17 1/2 miles long and is the most direct route to the New York World's Fair. The toll charge is 25c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: CHINATOWN, at the Bowery and Chatham Square, is New York's Oriental section.  Sight seeing busses will take visitors there from Times Square. Showing the Bloody Corner at Pell and Mott Streets which has been the place of countless murders caused by the rivalry of the Leong and Hip Sing Tongs.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: THE HAYDEN PLANETARIUM, which is located in the American Museum of Natural History at 81st Street and Central Park West can be seen "The Drama of the Skies." The most interesting feature of the Planetarium is the "Hall of the Sun." which shows the Solar System. There are six performances daily starting at 11 A. M. except Sunday and holidays. On these days the show starts at 10 A. M. The admission is 25c, 11 to 5 o'clock; evenings 8:30, 35c; 25c at 5 P. M. Saturday, Sunday and holidays. Children under 17 years of age 15c at all times. Reserved seats 50c and 60c.

Type_of_facilities: POINTS OF INTEREST IN NEW YORK CITY
Address: ROCKEFELLER CENTER  largest building project ever undertaken by private capital. Is situaed between 5th and 6th Avenue at 48th and 51st Streets, and occupies 12 acres. The tallest building in the group is the R. C. A. Building and is 70 stories tall and houses the National Broadcasting Co. On the West of Rockefeller Center is the Radio City Music Hall R. K. O. Building R. C. A. Building west and the Center Theatre, also Radio City which is named in honor of the Radio Corporation of America. On the Fifth Avenue side will be found the Le Maison Francaise, British Empire Building, Italian Building and the six story extension of the International Building.
